but being able to track that,

00:46:01.879 --> 00:46:04.639
like being able to track heart rate and blood pressure data

00:46:04.639 --> 00:46:07.239
and be able to start integrating that into EHRs

00:46:07.239 --> 00:46:10.000
and be able to connect all those pieces.

00:46:10.040 --> 00:46:13.919
The other thing that is personally very interesting to me

00:46:13.919 --> 00:46:15.199
is CGM data.

00:46:15.199 --> 00:46:17.840
So continuous glucose monitoring data for diabetes.

00:46:17.840 --> 00:46:19.919
My wife is a type one diabetic.

00:46:19.919 --> 00:46:22.679
And so she is a user, a patient,

00:46:22.679 --> 00:46:25.399
using a continuous glucose monitor.

00:46:25.399 --> 00:46:28.679
And to be able to integrate that more holistically

00:46:28.679 --> 00:46:30.840
with her provider's EHR is something

00:46:30.840 --> 00:46:32.959
that I think is really, really interesting.

00:46:32.959 --> 00:46:35.320
And if I manage to help be part of providing that,

00:46:35.320 --> 00:46:37.280
that'll be very, very cool.

00:46:37.280 --> 00:46:39.919
But I would love to be able to provide that

00:46:40.840 --> 00:46:42.280
because the doctor's gonna run an A1C and say,

00:46:42.280 --> 00:46:44.879
oh, so Mrs. Cohen, it looks like blah, blah, blah.

00:46:44.879 --> 00:46:46.439
But to be able to then,

00:46:46.439 --> 00:46:49.520
and right now he has to go to a completely separate system.

00:46:49.520 --> 00:46:53.199
He has to log into a separate system

00:46:53.199 --> 00:46:55.639
and he can't put those two pieces together.

00:46:55.639 --> 00:46:57.520
So yeah, I think to be able to connect those

00:46:57.520 --> 00:47:00.360
is where ambulatory care has to get too quickly

00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:03.159
to really take it to the next level of patient care.

00:47:05.040 --> 00:47:06.560
Sadly, I'm not doing that yet.

00:47:07.320 --> 00:47:08.159
Thanks, Andy.

00:47:09.959 --> 00:47:12.040
Another anonymous question was,

00:47:12.040 --> 00:47:15.639
are you monitoring for outbreaks like respiratory viruses

00:47:15.639 --> 00:47:19.479
or micros that could spread easily in a hospital setting?

00:47:19.479 --> 00:47:21.600
