00:53:33.520 --> 00:53:36.439
The other side that we're a little bit more active on

00:53:36.439 --> 00:53:41.439
is actually diabetes becoming the output, the consequence,

00:53:41.439 --> 00:53:44.560
is trying to go, so here are patients with pre-diabetes.

00:53:44.560 --> 00:53:47.399
Of all those that we know who have pre-diabetes,

00:53:47.399 --> 00:53:50.439
who are the most at risk of becoming diabetics

00:53:50.439 --> 00:53:52.040
in the next three to five years?

00:53:52.040 --> 00:53:54.719
So it's, I know I'm flipping the question on its head,

00:53:54.719 --> 00:53:57.120
but that is this idea of disease progression

00:53:57.120 --> 00:53:58.679
being going up to diabetes

00:53:58.679 --> 00:54:00.879
and actually being formally diagnosed with diabetes

00:54:00.879 --> 00:54:02.520
instead of just pre-diabetes.

00:54:02.520 --> 00:54:04.800
And then if you have diabetes,

00:54:04.800 --> 00:54:06.719
initially you would have,

00:54:06.719 --> 00:54:08.439
if you developed diabetes in that regard,

00:54:08.439 --> 00:54:09.679
you're a type two.

00:54:09.679 --> 00:54:12.520
And so you'd have uncomplicated type two diabetes.

00:54:12.520 --> 00:54:15.760
And eventually, as the disease progresses,

00:54:15.760 --> 00:54:18.399
those patients are gonna start developing,

00:54:18.399 --> 00:54:19.600
it can impact your kidneys

00:54:19.600 --> 00:54:22.439
and lead to chronic kidney disease, things like that.

00:54:22.439 --> 00:54:24.639
So there's opportunities in modeling around

00:54:24.639 --> 00:54:26.800
who is most at risk for things,

00:54:26.800 --> 00:54:29.199
for consequences of that with diabetes.

00:54:29.199 --> 00:54:32.639
And any chronic disease, be it, you know,

00:54:33.639 --> 00:54:36.040
asthma, what have you, can have, you know,

00:54:36.040 --> 00:54:38.520
side effects that are holistic and systemic.

